  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nDuring the builder health checks we lock the head 3 times:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/693886b94176faa4cb450f024696cb69cda2fe58/beacon_node/beacon_chain/src/beacon_chain.rs#L5705-L5708\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/693886b94176faa4cb450f024696cb69cda2fe58/beacon_node/beacon_chain/src/beacon_chain.rs#L5736-L5738\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/693886b94176faa4cb450f024696cb69cda2fe58/beacon_node/beacon_chain/src/beacon_chain.rs#L5741-L5745\r\n\r\n## Steps to resolve\r\n\r\nWe could load the cached head once at the start of the function and reuse that value. This doesn't require us to _hold_ the lock, the cached head is a small value that's cheap to copy (its large parts are behind an `Arc`).\r\n",
